The paper discusses the theory and applications of autoassociative fuzzy morphological memories for face recognition, which involves neural networks and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on image recognition, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the memory networks, which is related to machine learning and falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of fuzzy logic, which is related to artificial intelligence and falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the noise tolerance of the memory networks, which is related to information theory and falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
